{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17651389","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17651389"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T21:23:02+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T21:23:02+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18447"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18447","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18447"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11176"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114753"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11176","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11176"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18447"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96756"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4948"},{"type":"tags","id":"7710"},{"type":"tags","id":"7712"},{"type":"tags","id":"7835"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25922"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25926"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114753","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/114753"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA medical researcher collects the following data on patient waiting times (in minutes) in an emergency department: 15, 245, 35, 42, 28, 180, 33, 30.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the median waiting time when calculated using Microsoft Excel\u0027s MEDIAN function?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["41 minutes","28 minutes","79 minutes","34 minutes","45 minutes"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe data appears to be right-skewed due to a few very long waiting times.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETo find the median value, Excel\u0027s MEDIAN function can be used - this first arranges the numbers in ascending order: 15, 28, 30, 33, 35, 42, 180, 245. With eight values (an even number), the median is calculated as the average of the two middle numbers (33 + 35)/2 = \u003Cstrong\u003E34 minutes.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe median is more appropriate than the mean for this skewed dataset because it is not influenced by the extreme waiting times of 180 and 245 minutes.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The median is the preferred measure of central tendency for skewed data as it is not affected by extreme values.","In Microsoft Excel, the MEDIAN function calculates the middle value after sorting data in ascending order.","For datasets with an even number of values, the median is calculated as the average of the two middle numbers."],"references":["Sullivan LM. Essentials of biostatistics in public health. 3rd ed. Burlington (MA): Jones \u0026 Bartlett Learning; 2018.","Dawson B, Trapp RG. Basic \u0026 clinical biostatistics. 4th ed. New York: McGraw-Hill; 2004."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96756"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18447"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96756","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/96756"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-19T20:28:44+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-19T20:28:44+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11176"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"114753"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":nul